==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dittany
<hw>Dit"ta*ny</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>dytane</ets>, <ets>detane</ets>, <ets>dytan</ets>, OF.
<ets>ditain</ets>, F. <ets>dictame</ets>, L. <ets>dictamnum</ets>, fr.
Gr. <grk>di`ktamnon</grk> , <grk>di`ktamnos</grk>, a plant growing in
abundance on Mount <ets>Dicte</ets> in Crete. Cf.
<er>Dittander</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A plant
of the Mint family (<spn>Origanum Dictamnus</spn>), a native of
Crete.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The <spn>Dictamnus Fraxinella</spn>. See
<er>Dictamnus</er>.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>In America, the <spn>Cunila
Mariana</spn>, a fragrant herb of the Mint family.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

